===subject:Antifederalist and Federalist
===from:Lorena Lockhart
===date:Sun Feb 16 17:39:07 2003
===message:I believe that the Antifederalist did not know if this new form of government, check and balance, would benefit them but they felt that the common person was excluded from the plan. I do agree that the Federalist painted a picture perfect painting of a new government with all the trimmings but when the Antifederalist looked at the painting they did not see the common people the only people that they saw were the upper class. After the war for independence the Antifederalist did not wanted to try something that could possible take them back to where they fought so hard to come.
